.TH BAUDZILLA422 1 "2025" "Baudzilla 1.0" "RS422 Test Tool"
.SH NAME
baudzilla422 \- RS422 loopback and protocol test tool

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B baudzilla422
-p <port> -l <logfile> -s <string>
[-v] [-b <baud>] [-n <loops>] [-t <timeout>]
[--length <bytes>]
[--pattern ascii|hex|random|walking|checker]
[--linecheck] [--modbus] [--iec101] [--all]

.SH DESCRIPTION
Baudzilla422 tests an RS422 port using configurable patterns, loopback
verification, idle line noise detection, Modbus RTU probing and IEC101
probing.

Loopback mode requires TX and RX lines to be physically bridged.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B -v
Verbose output.

.TP
.B -p <port>
Serial port (e.g. /dev/ttyS1).

.TP
.B -l <logfile>
Log file.

.TP
.B -s <string>
ASCII base string for ASCII pattern.

.TP
.B -b <baud>
Baudrate (default 9600).

.TP
.B -n <loops>
Number of iterations.

.TP
.B -t <timeout>
Timeout seconds.

.TP
.B --length <bytes>
Payload length (default 64).

.TP
.B --pattern <name>
Pattern mode: ascii hex random walking checker.

.TP
.B --linecheck
Check idle line for noise.

.TP
.B --modbus
Run Modbus RTU probe (unit 1, function 3).

.TP
.B --iec101
Run IEC101 probe.

.TP
.B --all
Enable linecheck, Modbus and IEC101.

.TP
.B -h, --help
Show help.

.SH EXAMPLE
baudzilla422 -v -p /dev/ttyS1 -l log.txt -s "RS422" --pattern ascii --modbus --iec101

